ATTENTION COLLECTORS!!!
See info below:
1954 smith and wesson m13 aircrew man 
.38 SPC
$3500.00 (cash, credit/debit +3.5%, M.O.)

This is a very scarce revolver for the military collector! 
"This is a Smith & Wesson M13 "Aircrewman" that was made for the United Stated Air Force in 1954. Chambered for the .38 Special cartridge, these revolvers were built on an alloy K-frame and feature 6-shot aluminum alloy cylinders as well. The early test/evaluation guns had a 5-screw frame, "Aircrewman" marked barrels, Air Force medallion stocks, and a special serial number range. After the initial run and subsequent adoption some changes were made to the M13. Among these modifications were the deletion of the upper sideplate screw (note that this change occurred in the Aircrewman before the same change occurred in the commercial revolvers in 1955), deletion of the name "Aircrewman" from the right side of the barrel, deletion of the U.S. Air Force emblem from the stock medallions (replaced by standard S&W monogram), and the serial numbers were mixed among standard commercial production. This is one of the "standard production" M13's with the later features. The top strap is correctly marked "REVOLVER, LIGHTWEIGHT, M13", the back strap is marked "PROPERTY OF U.S. AIR FORCE", and the left side of the frame has the single "P" military proof marking."
This revolver:
very good condition
The serial numbered parts are all matching 
The revolver retains most of the original anodized finish with some normal handling and thinning
The stocks are in very good shape with some handling wear but no cracks
The mechanics are in good working order
The bore is very good with bright, sharp rifling.
